{% extends "base.html.twig" %}
{% block contents %}
<article class="home-hero row">
    <div class="promo col-md-6">
        <h2>Design, measure and track your experiments.</h2>
        <p>Building a product or trying to achieve a personal goal, we experiment every single day. Let's track these!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="create col-md-6">
        <form method="post" action="{{ path('create_experiment') }}">
            <div class="form-group">
                <label for="newExperiment">What's your experiment?</label>
                <input type="text" name="name" class="form-control" id="newExperiment" placeholder="Example: Use a tool to track my experiments...">
            </div>
            <button class="btn">Get started</button>
        </form>
    </div>
</article>
{% if experiments | length > 0 %}
<h3>Your experiments</h3>
<div class="experiments d-flex flex-wrap">
{% for experiment in experiments %}
    <div class="card experiment-card">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">{{ experiment.name }}</h5>
            <h6 class="card-subtitle mb-2 text-muted">
                {% if experiment.isStarted() %}
                    On-going.
                {% else %}
                    Not started.
                {% endif %}
            </h6>
        </div>
        <ul class="list-group list-group-flush experiment-outcomes">
            {% for expectedOutcome in experiment.expectedOutcomes %}
            <li class="list-group-item">
                <span class="experiment-name">{{ expectedOutcome.name }}</span>
                <span class="experiment-transition">{{ expectedOutcome.currentValue }} âžŸ {{ expectedOutcome.expectedValue }}</span>
            </li>
            {% endfor %}
        </ul>
        <div class="card-footer">
            <a href="{{ path('experiment', {'id': experiment.uuid}) }}" class="card-link">Open experiment</a>
        </div>
    </div>
{% endfor %}
</div>
<hr/>
{% endif %}
<article class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h4><i class="fa fa-key"></i> Measurable results</h4>
        <p>When creating an experiment, you set a number of measurable <em>expected</em> outcomes. These will help you to conclude whether the experiment is successful or not.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h4><i class="far fa-clock"></i> Track them over-time</h4>
        <p>Every week, we will send you an overview of your on-going experiments and invite you to <em>check-in</em> to update the measurable expected outcomes.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h4><i class="fa fa-users"></i> Collaborate</h4>
        <p>Invite as many collaborators as you'd like to collaborate on your experiments. They will also be notified when something happens to the experimentation.</p>
    </div>
</article>
{% endblock %}
